9 An Act relating to food truck fire suppression;
amending Section 1, Chapter 106, O.S.L. 2024, as
10 amended by Section 1, Chapter 342, O.S.L. 2025 (74
O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 325.20), which relates to
11 mobile food establishments, fire and life safety code
compliance, permit, inspection, and rules; modifying
12 mandate for automatic fire extinguishing system in
food trucks; removing expiration date; and providing
13 an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 106, O.S.L.
18 2024, as amended by Section 1, Chapter 342, O.S.L. 2025 (74 O.S.
19 Supp. 2025, Section 325.20), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 325.20. A. All mobile food preparation vehicles
21 operating within this state prior to July 1, 2024, that are capable
22 of producing smoke or grease-laden vapors shall be in compliance
23 with the most current adopted fire code. With, with the exception
24 of an automatic fire extinguishing system, such which shall be
Req. No. 16208 Page 1

1 opti onal, if the mobile food preparation vehicle is equipped with at
2 least two portable fire extinguishers meeting NFPA 10 standards and
3 all employees receive documented annual fire safety training
4 approved by the State Fire Marshal. Such requirement shall apply to
5 vehicles including, but not limited to, vehicles utilizing electric
6 energy, liquefied petroleum gas, compressed natural gas, or a
7 combination thereof for cooking, provided that portable fire
8 extinguishers are installed and maintained in accordance with the
9 most current version of NFPA 10: Standard for Portable Fire
10 Extinguishers. A six-liter Class K-rated, portable fire
11 extinguisher is required for all cooking equipment involving solid
12 fuels, vegetable or animal oils and fats, or a combination thereof.
13 All portable fire extinguishers shall be in clear view and
14 immediately available for use.
15 B. All mobile food preparation vehicles utilizing, handling, or
16 transporting liquefied petroleum gas or any liquefied petroleum gas
17 system, equipment, container, apparatus, or appliance shall receive
18 and maintain a permit from, and be inspected annually by, the
19 Oklahoma Liquefied Petroleum Gas Administration or its employees, in
20 conjunction with the Oklahoma Liquified Petroleum Gas Board. The
21 Board shall promulgate rules related to such permits including
22 inspection requirements. The State Fire Marshal issuing shall issue
23 an annual operation permit decal to mobile food preparation
24 vehicles.
Req. No. 16208 Page 2

1 C. The provisions in subsection A of this section shall expire
2 on January 1, 2026, and all mobile food preparation vehicles shall
3 comply with the most current adopted fire codes set forth by this
4 state.
5 D. Mobile food preparation vehicles shall be under the
6 jurisdiction of the State Fire Marshal for fire and life safety code
7 compliance and shall be inspected annually by the State Fire Marshal
8 to ensure compliance with the latest version of the state-adopted
9 minimum codes for fire and life safety as adopted by the Oklahoma
10 Uniform Building Code Commission. The State Fire Marshal shall
11 coordinate, at minimum, annual inspections conducted:
12 1. Within each of the four quadrants of this state; and
13 2. Twice within each county with a population exceeding four
14 hundred thousand (400,000) according to the latest Federal Decennial
15 Census.
16 E. D. Upon approval, the State Fire Marshal shall issue an
17 operational permit decal indicating that the vehicle meets the
18 minimum fire and life safety code requirements adopted at the time
19 of inspection.
20 F. E. Nothing in this section shall prevent:
21 1. The State Fire Marshal from enforcing the minimum fire code
22 requirements as allowed by law and revoking the operations of a
23 mobile food preparation vehicle for cause when such vehicle is
24
Req. No. 16208 Page 3

1 dete rmined to be inherently dangerous to the health, safety, or
2 welfare of persons within this state;
3 2. A political subdivision from enforcing the event permits,
4 operational fees, land use regulations, zoning, or other ordinances
5 in relation to the operation of a mobile food preparation vehicle
6 within the boundaries of the political subdivision; or
7 3. The State Department of Health from licensing and regulating
8 mobile food preparation vehicles as provided by the provisions of
9 Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes and rules promulgated by the State
10 Commissioner of Health.
11 G. F. The State Fire Marshal may promulgate rules necessary to
12 implement the provisions of this section. Such rules shall have
13 uniform force and effect throughout this state and no political
14 subdivision or other agency shall enact or enforce any fire or life
15 safety code-related ordinances, rules, or other requirements for
16 mobile food preparation vehicles, except in a county with a
17 population exceeding four hundred thousand (400,000) according to
18 the latest Federal Decennial Census.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
